{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_016HJqkqoJrSG5YhUpv974Fk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The root cause is clear: `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')` takes the `connect_only` path (node.py:198), which reads `node_ip_address.json` from the client's *local* session dir — a file only written when a Ray node runs locally. The ray-client pod isn't a Ray node, so the file never exists. Let me confirm the file format and check how the session dir is derived."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1821,"cache_read_input_tokens":38497,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1821},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e45de645-afb0-4fb9-8a02-08e9c6536f4a","uuid":"f840da6f-3600-4aed-a594-4d04963a289b","request_id":"req_011CcASuzvvCtShQ9RG4EC5J"}
